// ===================================================================================================================================
// File          : StaffSteps.java  (consolidated)
// Package       : stepdefinitions.STAFF
// Description   : Single shared step-definition class backing every modernised BISS Staff
//                 (internal portal) E2E regression pack (TC_01_STAFF .. TC_17_STAFF in
//                 AllStaff.feature). Every repeated action across the legacy Staff feature files
//                 is defined ONCE here as a parameterised step and reused by all features.
//
//                 Conventions (aligned with the framework):
//                   - iAction() for every UI interaction
//                   - ObjReader.getLocator("key") for every locator lookup; parameterised keys
//                     carry a {TOKEN} placeholder replaced in-step via String.replace(...)
//                   - i-prefixed local variables, p-prefixed parameters
//                   - DataTable.asMap()/asMaps()/asList() for feature-supplied data
//                   - Per-step comment blocks (description, parameters, author, date)
//
//                 Data handling (matches TC_01_Login.java / Hooks.java):
//                   - URL      : launched by Hooks from the Config sheet - not handled here.
//                   - Username : supplied by the feature via the login step.
//                   - Password : resolved from TestData.xlsx "Password" column at runtime via the
//                                framework TD: mechanism (iAction value "TD:Password").
//                   - Herd / parcel / reference values supplied in-feature via DataTable.
//
//                 The framework's own steps "user on staff login page" and
//                 "user on OpenShift staff login page" live in the existing login glue and are
//                 intentionally NOT redefined here.
//
// Author        : Aniket Pathare | aniket.pathare@government.ie
// Date Created  : 14-07-2026
// ===================================================================================================================================

